        "title": "Types of upper partial Dentures you need to know.",
        "excerpt": "Sometimes you lose your teeth, but you don&#8217;t have to live like that because there are different upper Partial Dentures types available that you can consider to fill that gap in your mouth.\u00a0 Types of Partial Dentures types&nbsp;&nbsp; Following are the three types of upper Partial Dentures types:&nbsp; A very lightweight, thin thermoplastic material that [&hellip;]",
        "author": "Noble Dental Care",
        "content": "<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Sometimes you lose your teeth, but you don't have to live like that because there are different upper Partial Dentures types available that you can consider to fill that gap in your mouth.\u00a0<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Types of Partial Dentures types&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/h4>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Following are the three types of upper Partial Dentures types:&nbsp;<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true,\"start\":1} -->\n<ol start=\"1\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Flexible partial dentures\u00a0<\/strong><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ol>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A very lightweight, thin thermoplastic material that will get injected over the gums, so they cover them perfectly. No one might notice the presence of flexible partial dentures because you will have a natural look. The chances of getting any allergy after flexible partial dentures are nearly none.\u00a0<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>These partial dentures get support from the tissue attachment, and you can also use gum-colored clasps. The dentist will use those clasps, so no one will ever know that you have dentures in your mouth.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true,\"start\":2} -->\n<ol start=\"2\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Cast metal partial dentures\u00a0<\/strong><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ol>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One of the most common partial dentures is cast metal partial dentures. The dentist would use an ultra-thin, rigid metal base holding acrylic teeth. The metal clasp will attach the denture to your existing teeth.\u00a0\u00a0<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Cast metal partial dentures are a durable option because they last longer. You have to take proper care of them. You might feel a little uncomfortable or get an allergy if you are hypo-allergic to materials like metal. So, people with such problems shouldn't prefer getting cast metal partial dentures.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true,\"start\":3} -->\n<ol start=\"3\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Acrylic partial denture\u00a0<\/strong><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ol>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>First, the dentist will replace the teeth with a pink acrylic base. The pink acrylic base will minimize the risk of breakage, and the dentist will use a metal clasp to connect the base with the natural teeth.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The person who gets partial acrylic dentures might feel awkward because they get visible upon opening the mouth. There would be no problem chewing food anymore, and it is an inexpensive upper partial denture option.\u00a0\u00a0<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It would be a temporary solution before you get permanent alternative partial dentures like cast metal dentures. They will stay in their place for a few years if you take proper care of them.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":2393,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img src=\"https:\/\/nobledentalcares.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/160a.jpg\" alt=\"Types of upper partial Dentures you need to know.\" class=\"wp-image-2393\"\/><\/figure>\n<!-- \/wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Why do you have to get upper partial dentures?&nbsp;<\/h4>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Following are the reasons why you have to get upper partial dentures:&nbsp;<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Restore your ability to chew and talk\u00a0<\/h5>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When you lose a tooth, and you know it won't grow up again, then you start to suffer while eating and chewing food. You might not be able to talk correctly. The only solution for this problem would be getting partial dentures.\u00a0\u00a0<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Partial dentures will restore your ability to chew, eat and talk properly. There is no other way to fill the gap you have in your mouth. You won't be able to pronounce words properly with that gap.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Food particles will start to get stuck in the gap, and you will always feel the pain in your mouth. So, a big reason to get partial dentures would be to ease life. You get back to your normal routine of eating and talking.&nbsp;<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>You can smile after getting upper partial dentures&nbsp;<\/h5>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you don't have all the teeth in your mouth, you might not feel confident while smiling. You might start hiding your face, so no one will ever notice something missing from your mouth.&nbsp;<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You will require upper partial dentures to regain your confidence so you can talk freely and laugh freely. No one will ever notice that you have dentures if you consider flexible partial dentures. It would feel like all your teeth are natural, and you won't have to put a hand on your face whenever you want to smile or laugh.\u00a0<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>For even jaw structure&nbsp;<\/h5>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When you lose teeth, your mouth's jaw structure will be affected. If you don't get the solution right away, you might face other problems. To maintain the jaw structure of your teeth the way it was before you lost your tooth, you can consider getting partial dentures. It would keep the jaw structure even.&nbsp;<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Final Remarks<\/h4>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Now that you know the Partial Dentures types mentioned above, you can choose from them according to your need. You know why you must get your partial dentures, so you should delay getting them. Get partial dentures from the best dentist near you if you want them to last long.\u00a0<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/nobledentalcares.com\/contacts\/\">Contact<\/a>\u00a0your dentist in Union City, Dr. Zafar Sayeedi, at<a href=\"https:\/\/nobledentalcares.com\/\">\u00a0Noble Dental Care<\/a>\u00a0to know about the types of upper Partial Dentures.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Resource:\u00a0<\/h5>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/nobledentalcares.com\/blog\/a-guide-on-the-best-materials-for-full-partial-dentures\/\">A guide on the best materials for Full &amp; Partial Dentures.<\/a><\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>*This media\/content or any other on this website does not prescribe, recommend, or prevent any treatment or procedure. Therefore, we highly recommend that you get the advice of a qualified dentist or other medical practitioners regarding your specific dental condition*\u202f<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->",
