        "title": "All on Four vs. All on Six, which is a better dental implant?",
        "excerpt": "What is an all-on-four dental implant? What is an all-on-six dental implant? These are the question that people usually ask when their dentist suggests they get dental implants. While these make a permanent solution for the tooth that you lost, these also come with benefits for your remaining natural teeth. However, selecting between these options [&hellip;]",
        "author": "emily.brown@vigorant.com",
        "content": "<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>What is an all-on-four dental implant? What is an all-on-six dental implant? These are the question that people usually ask when their dentist suggests they get dental implants. While these make a permanent solution for the tooth that you lost, these also come with benefits for your remaining natural teeth.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>However, selecting between these options can be tricky, especially when you do not know their purpose and specific functionality. So, here you can learn about better dental implant types and decide which one will be better for you.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>What is an all-on-four dental implant?<\/h4>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"right\",\"id\":2137,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignright size-full\"><img src=\"https:\/\/nobledentalcares.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/07\/276.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2137\"\/><\/figure>\n<!-- \/wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>An all-on-four dental implant uses a combination of prosthetics with implants to secure teeth in place. Here patient gets 4 implants secured into the jawbone using the drilling process. After that, porcelain crowns get mounted on those implants.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Thus, the patient may get new artificial teeth that resemble natural teeth. When a patient gets an all-on-four dental implant, they can get multiple prosthetic teeth connected with each implant. So, there will be no need for multiple dentures for every tooth.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>What are the benefits of an all-on-four dental implant?<\/h4>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Getting an all-on-four implant brings several benefits, which are:<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>The natural feel and look of the prosthetic teeth because they are made with porcelain material. You may take some time to get used to these, but you will not notice them after a while.<\/li><li>With your jaw complete with teeth, you can eat and drink things that you normally did. You will not face chewing or crushing issues like when you miss a few teeth from your jaw.<\/li><li>This treatment surgery takes a short time to complete, and all of the missing teeth can be applied in a single surgery.<\/li><li>Getting an all-on-four dental implant is less painful than the bone grafting process. It is because of the advanced surgery process and shorter healing time.<\/li><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>What is an all-on-six dental implant?<\/h4>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>An all-on-six implant is not very different from all-on-four because the main concept is the same. However, instead of 4 implants in the other method, all six dental implant includes 6 implants.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>These 6 implants are placed in different areas of the mouth where the bone volume in the jaw is the highest. An all-on-six dental implant is a good treatment for patients with enough bone structure because it helps enhance the bone potential in the patient's mouth.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>What are the benefits of an all-on-six dental implant?<\/h4>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While most of the benefits of all six dental implants overlap with the other solution, some are different, and here we will be discussing those.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"right\",\"id\":2136,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignright size-full\"><img src=\"https:\/\/nobledentalcares.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/07\/274.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2136\"\/><\/figure>\n<!-- \/wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>The first benefit is that all-on-six implants may need some bone grafting. Thus, it retains natural bone to maximize the natural bone potential.<\/li><li>The patient may get instant results, which are long-lasting because these implants bring a permanent solution to the missing teeth.<\/li><li>The recovery process is quick here; the patient can use these prosthetics like their natural teeth for beautification and practical purposes.<\/li><li>Maintenance and cleaning are easier because of more implants resulting in better strength.<\/li><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Which dental implant is better for you?<\/h4>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Selecting between these 2 types of dental implants can be a little tricky for you. However, the decision will be easier when you know the condition of your jaw bone. The method with 6 implants is comparatively stronger and more stable. Thus, you get a long-lasting result. Remember that it needs the jaw bone to be stronger.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>On the other hand, the one with 4 implants also solves the problem, but the lack of stability, durability, and comfort may not make them the best choice. So, when you are making your final decision, always consult your views with your dentist so that you can get the treatment that brings you the best solution.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Conclusion<\/h4>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As you get dental implant surgery, you must get the treatment that solves all your tooth loss solutions. As everyone has a different dental condition, selecting the dental implant is better per your dental professional's suggestion. This way, you may get the most effective treatment and convenient experience.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/nobledentalcares.com\/contacts\/\">Contact<\/a>\u00a0your dentist in Union City, Dr. Zafar Sayeedi at<a href=\"https:\/\/nobledentalcares.com\/\">\u00a0Noble Dental Care<\/a>\u00a0to know about better dental implants.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>This media\/content or any other on this website does not prescribe, recommend, or prevent any treatment or procedure.\u202fTherefore, we\u202fhighly recommend that you get the advice of a qualified dentist or other medical practitioners regarding your specific dental condition<\/em>\u202f\u202f\u202f<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->",
        "date": "July 14, 2022",
